<h3>Dynamic Unit Map Table</h3>
<dl class='tweakbb_info'>
    <dt>Description</dt>
    <dd>
      <p>This tweak dynamically maps Blackboard resources (folders and links) into a table, based on their titles</p>
    </dd>
    <dt>Skill Level</dt>
    <dd>Medium (Optional HTML)</dd>
    <dt>How to Use</dt>
    <dd>
        <ol>
            <li>
              <p>Name your Resources / Blackboard Items (items, folders, links) in the following format</p>
              <p>"<span style='background:#FA88FF;'>row</span>"<b>:</b> "<span style='background:#FAFF88;'>column</span>"</p>
              <p><em>Examples:</em></p>
              <ul>
                <li>"<span style='background:#FA88FF;'>Week 1</span><b>:</b> <span style='background:#FAFF88;'>Lecture</span> Introduction to Schematics"</li>
                <li>"<span style='background:#FA88FF;'>Week 2</span><b>:</b> <span style='background:#FAFF88;'>Lecture</span> Schematics Process"</li>
                <li>"<span style='background:#FA88FF;'>Resources</span><b>:</b> <span style='background:#FAFF88;'>Readings</span> Future Workforce"</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>Create a new Blackboard item named <b>Unit Map</b>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>In the text editor, create a table with the right number of rows and columns for your content.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>Type into this table the <span style='background:#FAFF88;'>column</span> and <span style='background:#FA88FF;'>row</span> names that you used on your Blackboard Items, leaving the first upper-left cell blank.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>Save and check your table.  The tweak will move items titled in the <span style='background:#FA88FF;'>row</span>"<b>:</b> "<span style='background:#FAFF88;'>column</span> format to the corresponding cells in the table.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
				<p><em>Optional:</em> This tweak has a few extra options for changing the colour, highlighting, collapsing rows into modules and more.  Click the detailed examples link below for more information.</p>
    </dd>
</dl>